# Ubuntu Server – Technical Evaluation

## Overview
Ubuntu Server is a stable, widely used server distribution based on Debian, optimized for cloud, enterprise, and virtualization.

## Installation Experience
- Text-based installer straightforward to follow.
- LTS version provides long-term support and security updates.

## Strengths
- Very strong community support.
- Excellent hardware and cloud compatibility.
- Easy to deploy for beginners and professionals.

## Limitations
- Heavier footprint than minimal server distributions.
- Some services preinstalled that may not be needed.

## Best Use Cases
✓ Web servers  
✓ Virtual machines  
✓ Cloud deployments (AWS, OCI, Azure)  
✓ Enterprise workloads

